            "body": "This doesn't seem like a bug to me? If an attacker can modify `PATH` it's already over, completely unrelated to Nvim. This is why `export PATH=\".:$PATH\"` is considered an antipattern.\n\nIf this counts as an attack, I think every bash script I've ever written is vulnerable :)",
